<div id="banner">
	<h1>TinyURL</h1>
</div>

<div class="content">
<p><a href="http://tinyurl.com/">TinyURL.com - where tiny is better!</a> [via <a href="http://boingboing.net/2002_05_01_archive.html#85124180">MarkF</a>]</p>

<p>Not only are these URLs shorter than MakeAShorterLink, but they&#8217;re real redirects, and even let you point deeper inside a site. For example, if you set up your site to be http://tinyurl.com/3 then you can use http://tinyurl.com/3/my-links-page.html to link to your links page.</p>

<form action="http://tinyurl.com/create.php" method="post" target="_blank">
